Inventory Management System

Project Overview

The Inventory Management System is a web-based application developed to monitor, organize, and control stock levels within a business or organization. The system enables users to manage products, suppliers, categories, purchases, and sales in an efficient and centralized manner.

This project improves stock accuracy, reduces manual errors, and provides real-time inventory information for better business decision-making.

---

Problem Statement

Traditional inventory management methods often rely on manual records and spreadsheets, which can lead to stock mismatches, product shortages, overstocking, data entry errors, and inefficient operations. Businesses require an intelligent and automated system to manage inventory effectively and support smooth business processes.

The Inventory Management System addresses these challenges by providing a reliable and user-friendly solution for tracking and controlling stock.

